---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import PageHero from "../components/PageHero.astro";
const pageTitle = "About Me";
---

<BaseLayout pageTitle={pageTitle}>
  <PageHero
    kicker="About"
    title="Roger Rajaratnam"
    subtitle="Software engineer & technical lead based in London"
  />

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container is-max-desktop">
      <div class="content post__content">
        <p>
          I'm a software engineer and technical lead based in London, passionate
          about building things on the web and solving problems through
          technology. My journey into software engineering started with a
          curiosity about how digital products work behind the scenes — that
          curiosity eventually turned into a career focused on designing and
          building scalable applications.
        </p>

        <p>
          Over the years, I've worked across a range of projects in fintech and
          consumer technology, primarily as a full-stack engineer. I enjoy
          working across the entire stack, from crafting intuitive front-end
          experiences to designing backend systems that are reliable, scalable,
          and maintainable. Much of my work today sits at the intersection of
          engineering, architecture, and leadership — helping teams build
          high-quality software while also thinking about the bigger technical
          picture.
        </p>

        <p>
          One of the most rewarding aspects of my career has been helping other
          developers grow. I've spent time mentoring engineers and teaching at
          coding bootcamps, supporting people as they transition into software
          engineering and develop their skills. Watching someone go from writing
          their first lines of code to confidently building applications is
          incredibly fulfilling.
        </p>

        <p>
          I studied Computer Software Engineering at the University of
          Westminster, which gave me the foundations that shaped my path into
          full-stack development. Since then, I've had the opportunity to work
          with different teams, technologies, and products — each experience
          teaching me something new about building software and collaborating
          with others.
        </p>

        <p>
          This blog is a place where I share ideas, lessons learned, and
          practical insights from my experience in software engineering.
          Sometimes that might mean writing about system design, web
          development, or technical leadership. Other times it might simply be
          reflections on things I've learned along the way.
        </p>

        <p>
          Outside of work, I'm always exploring new technologies, thinking about
          better ways to build software, and staying curious about how the web
          continues to evolve.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
